The paper focuses on object classification using sparse signal processing and learning algorithms, which is a key area of research in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.LG). The paper also discusses optimization problems for learning dictionary and structured sparse representations, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper applies these algorithms to medical imaging (cs.NA) and ultra-wideband synthetic aperture radar (cs.RF), but these are less likely categories as they are more specific subfields within computer science.
